 have people in the zone to kill him....well, now who is not respecting people.  The person hogging the spawn by kiting it around and keeping it from a group of people well capable of killing it, or the people that are ready and willing to kill the mob and their only interuption is someone running around the zone with agro (but without people) shouting the claim.<br><br>To me it would be less respectfull for me to kite a mob around and stop someone from killing it (just so I could w/ my friends).  That is just my point of view.  Take it for what you will, I play EQ and I treat my fellow's in the game as respectfully as I know.<br><br>Nodda:  I hunt in chardok, CT, Ahkeva(sp?), Maidens, Umbral, DN, and SG mostly, if you want to hang around with me you are welcome and if you see me kiting anything there then you are welcome to the mob.  I have not logged in in a while so you might find it hard to catch me online though  ;-)<br><br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458><b>Balise</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uauram.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Auram</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Man and Moon</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 10:22:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=698.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   a</span><hr size=1> &quot;mobs agro people wandering by, but that doesnt mean it was engaged&quot;<br><br>I'm pretty sure he wasn't just &quot;wandering by&quot;<br><br>-Auram Moracant (retired)<br>Clan Skallagrim <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ueuphoric17.showPublicProfile?language=EN>euphoric17</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba